-- Hering, Interconexion Electrica, Usiminas: Latin America Equity Preview
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2010-09-28T05:57:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/hering-interconexion-electrica-masisa-usiminas-latin-america-equity.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Latin American trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous
close.  The  MSCI Latin America Index  gained 0.8 percent to 4,284.95.
In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-traded class of
stock.  Brazil  Cia. Hering  (HGTX3 BZ): The Brazilian textile company said
it may increase a plan to open new stores, saying it has an
estimated potential for 604 stores in the country, according to
a regulatory filing. The shares rose 5.2 percent to 73.6 reais.  Usinas Siderurgicas de Minas Gerais SA  (USIM5 BZ): Brazil’s
second-biggest steelmaker approved a two-for-one stock split,
according to a regulatory filing. The shares rose 1.5 percent to
22.5 reais.  Chile  Masisa SA  (MASISA CC): Chile’s national statistics
institute may report today that industrial production rose 4.3
percent in August from a year earlier, according to the median
estimate of 13 economists in a Bloomberg Survey. The Santiago-
based wood panels maker climbed 2.1 percent to 83.02 pesos.  Colombia  Interconexion Electrica SA  (ISA CB): The Colombian state-
controlled energy company known as Isa said it plans to bid for
rights to a transmission line project in Cotaruse, Peru,
according to a statement on the website of Colombia’s securities
regulator. The shares rose 1.5 percent to 13,900 pesos.  To contact the reporters on this story:
